{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a portion of which has already been restituted. While the breach of trust is serious, a 10-year sentence requested by the public is disproportionate to sentencing guidelines for this amount and lack of criminal history. A 6-month sentence serves as a sufficient deterrent, punishes the criminal act, and allows for continued restitution efforts.",
  "verdict": 6
}
